libBERT
------------------------------------------
libBERT is a C library for encoding and decoding BERT (Binary ERlang Term)
data. Inspired by the Ruby BERT library, libBERT aims to provide the full BERT
format to C programmers.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.33-1
  libBERT0-0.1.0+git20131127-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.24.51-6
  cmake-2.8.12.2-3
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/postmodern/libBERT

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/postmodern/libBERT.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libBERT-0.1.0+git20131127-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libBERT-0.1.0+git20131127-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libBERT-0.1.0+git20131127-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libBERT-0.1.0+git20131127-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libBERT0-0.1.0+git20131127-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libBERT-devel-0.1.0+git20131127-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libBERT)
  /usr/bin/bert_dump.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libBERT.README
  /usr/share/doc/libBERT/ChangeLog.txt
  /usr/share/doc/libBERT/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/libBERT/README.txt

(libBERT0)
  /usr/bin/cygBERT-0.dll

(libBERT-devel)
  /usr/include/bert.h
  /usr/include/bert/config.h
  /usr/include/bert/data.h
  /usr/include/bert/decoder.h
  /usr/include/bert/dict.h
  /usr/include/bert/encoder.h
  /usr/include/bert/errno.h
  /usr/include/bert/list.h
  /usr/include/bert/magic.h
  /usr/include/bert/regex.h
  /usr/include/bert/tuple.h
  /usr/include/bert/types.h
  /usr/include/bert/util.h
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libBERT.pc

